-- Linc Energy, Macquarie, Sigma, Santos, Woodside: Australian, N.Z. Stocks
-- Shani Raja
-- 2010-08-02T06:36:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/linc-energy-macquarie-sigma-santos-woodside-australian-n-z-stocks.html

          
          
             Australia’s  S&P/ASX 200 Index  rose
1.1 percent to 4,541.60 at the 4:10 p.m. close of trading in
Sydney. New Zealand’s  NZX 50 Index  advanced 0.3 percent to
3,044.17 at the 5 p.m. close in Wellington.  
 The following were among the most active shares in the
market today. Stock symbols are in parentheses after company
names.  
      Downer EDI Ltd.  (DOW AU) slumped 6.2 percent to A$4.66
after making a profit statement. The company, which also
appointed  Grant Fenn  as managing director after the resignation
of  Geoff Knox  on July 30, said it expects full-year net income
of about A$3 million.  
    Linc Energy Ltd.  (LNC AU) jumped 19 percent to A$1.89 after
the Australian energy company seeking to sell coal projects said
it remains in talks with companies including Adani Enterprises
Ltd. about the sale. Energy World Corp. (EWC AU), an Australian
gas and electricity developer, climbed 9.9 percent to 50
Australian cents.  
   Macquarie Group Ltd.  (MQG AU) rose 1.3 percent to A$37.67.
Australia’s biggest investment bank was raised to “buy” from
“neutral” by analysts at UBS AG.  
    Sigma Pharmaceuticals Ltd.  (SIP AU) surged 4.6 percent to
45.5 Australian cents. Sigma may have attracted a new bidder for
its A$600 million generics business, with U.S.-based Watson
Pharmaceuticals considering an offer for the division, the
Sydney Morning Herald reported, without saying where it got the
information.  
 New Zealand:  
 Freightways Ltd.  (FRE NZ), New Zealand’s second-biggest
courier company, gained 1.1 percent to NZ$2.85 after  being
rated “buy” in new coverage at Deutsche Bank AG.  
